<BaseLayout
  title="About — Shelly Xiong"
  description="Shelly Xiong is a NYC birder on a Linnaean Society committee and NYC Bird Alliance volunteer. Illustration, writing, and software for birders."
>
  <main style="padding-top: calc(var(--nav-height) + 40px);">
    <section class="section about" id="about">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
        <div class="about-grid">
          <div class="about-text">
            <p>I'm Shelly. I watch birds in New York City.</p>
            <p>That sentence is more interesting than it sounds. New York has more migratory bird traffic than almost anywhere on the East Coast — Central Park alone sees over 270 species in a given year, from a Bronx-born peregrine to a woodcock who definitely shouldn't be in midtown. I keep a public eBird profile, post what I see across the five boroughs, and share what I'm learning as I go.</p>
            <p>I'm on a committee of the <strong><a href="https://www.linnaeannewyork.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Linnaean Society of New York</a></strong> — the oldest birding organization in New York, founded in 1878. I volunteer with the <strong><a href="https://nycbirdalliance.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NYC Bird Alliance</a></strong> (the region's largest). My photos have appeared in the Linnaean Society's field trip reports. I also illustrate what I see and build small software tools to answer questions I have about the city's birds — like when exactly each warbler shows up in May.</p>
            <p>Outside of birds I work in software — currently as a Website Administrator at the <a href="https://www.metmuseum.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Metropolitan Museum of Art</a>. I draw a lot. I'm teaching myself risograph printing. My online handle has been <strong><a href="/#contact">@shellylynnx</a></strong> for long enough that even I can't remember why.</p>
            <p>If you want to work together — press, partnerships, commissions, speaking, walks, development, or any of the usual — email <a href="mailto:helloshellylynnx@gmail.com">helloshellylynnx@gmail.com</a>.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="about-interests">
            <h3>Credentials &amp; affiliations</h3>
